My original DP solution:
https://leetcode.com/problems/domino-and-tromino-tiling/discuss/116534

**Imagine we are looking at the `i`th column, all previous columns have been fully tiled.**

**There are three possible states at the ith column**

**1. BOTH TOP AND BOTTOM CELLS ARE EMPTY**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/d71ff7e3-b01a-4466-aa30-dcd6c9bef79c_1605052246.083369.png)

**2. ONLY THE BOTTOM CELL IS EMPTY** (green block = used cell)

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/01adb44e-a3fa-4735-b0f0-ac763547896d_1605052289.985583.png)

**3. ONLY THE TOP CELL IS EMPTY** (green block = used cell)

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/c09c7572-961f-4483-9504-d1ed7bdeb911_1605052313.539652.png)

**WHEN BOTH CELLS EMPTY (STATE 1)**

**At the current column, we can use**

- One vertical domino
	- **after using it at `i`th column, we need to calculate `i + 1`th column at state 1** (at `i + 1` both cells are still empty)
- OR two horizontal dominos
	- **then we calculate `i + 2`th at state 1** (each horizontal domino takes two columns, at `i + 2` both cells are empty)
- OR a L tromino
	- **then calculate `i+1` at state 3 above** after using it, at `i + 1` the bottom cell will be used.
- OR a flipped L tromino
	- **then calculate `i+1` at state 2 above** after using it, at `i + 1` the top cell will be used.

**For state 1, the total number of ways is the sum of all four posibilities**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/aa2b11c4-7ca8-4a00-9e31-b04ab949dcd6_1605052038.9683368.png)

**WHEN BOTTOM CELL EMPTY (STATE 2)**

**we can use**

- one horizontal tile at the bottom
	- **after using it, we need to calculate `i+1` at state 3**, bottom cell of `i+1` is used
- one horizontally flipped L tromino
	- **after using it, we need to calculate `i+2` at state 1**, both top and bottom cells at `i+2` are empty, L tromino takes two columns, hence `i + 2`

**Total number of ways is the sum of both possibilities**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/33acc706-5062-411c-8277-552770f1be1b_1605052136.7791326.png)

**WHEN TOP CELL EMPTY (STATE 3)**

**we can use**

- one horizontal tile at the top
	- **after using it, we need to calculate `i+1` at state 2**, top cell of `i+1` is used
- one flipped L tromino
	- **after using it, we need to calculate `i+2` at state 1**, both top and bottom cells at `i+2` are empty, L tromino takes two columns, hence `i + 2`

**Total number of ways is the sum of both possibilities**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/93b1a388-ca1f-441b-aa74-d73a9d439c69_1605052179.572588.png)

**We just need to recursively solve the same problem at each index.**

**Implementation**
```javascript
function rc (n, index = 0, state = 'topBottomFree') {
    if (index >= n) return state === 'topBottomFree' && index === n ? 1 : 0;
    switch (state) {
        case 'topBottomFree':
            const useVerticalDomino = rc(n, index + 1, 'topBottomFree');
            const useTwoHorizontalDomino = rc(n, index + 2, 'topBottomFree');
            const useTopTromino = rc(n, index + 1, 'bottomFree');
            const useBottomTromino = rc(n, index + 1, 'topFree');
            return useVerticalDomino + useTwoHorizontalDomino + useTopTromino + useBottomTromino;
        case 'bottomFree':
            const useHorizontallyFlippedBottomTromino = rc(n, index + 2, 'topBottomFree');
            const useHorizontalDominoAtBottom = rc(n, index + 1, 'topFree');
            return useHorizontallyFlippedBottomTromino + useHorizontalDominoAtBottom;
        case 'topFree':
            const useHorizontallyFlippedTopTromino = rc(n, index + 2, 'topBottomFree');
            const useHorizontalDominoAtTop = rc(n, index + 1, 'bottomFree');
            return useHorizontallyFlippedTopTromino + useHorizontalDominoAtTop;
    }
}
```

**Add memoisation, there are only 3 states at each index, complexity O(3n)**
```javascript
function rc2 (n, index = 0, state = 0, memo = {}) {
    if (index >= n) return state === 0 && index === n ? 1 : 0;

    const memoKey = `${index},${state}`;
    if (memo[memoKey] !== undefined) return memo[memoKey];

    switch (state) {
        case 0:
            return memo[memoKey] = (rc2(n, index + 1, 0, memo) + rc2(n, index + 2, 0, memo) + rc2(n, index + 1, 1, memo) + rc2(n, index + 1, 2, memo)) % 1000000007;
        case 1:
            return memo[memoKey] = (rc2(n, index + 2, 0, memo) + rc2(n, index + 1, 2, memo)) % 1000000007;
        case 2:
            return memo[memoKey] = (rc2(n, index + 2, 0, memo) + rc2(n, index + 1, 1, memo)) % 1000000007;
    }
}
```

