**Idea?**
* *Dynamic Programming*
* **dp[i] = number of ways to form 2 x i board with gives tiles.**
* Suppose, we had already calculated the dp[j] for all j belongs to [1,i-1], Now how to get dp[i] ?
* Let's look out certain domino we can place at 'i'th position.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/0d9a6e41-89e5-4a89-ba4c-92af0f4a9527_1639123044.4028025.png)

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/53cb9214-7591-45db-b6cc-6c1eb556c92c_1639123069.2442987.png)

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/36e79f50-4eb3-4abc-b0fd-f72004a08792_1639123084.2648911.png)

**Generating dp relation:-**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/072039ac-2f71-43c2-a2a7-6ea930e4bbfc_1639132061.445384.png)


**Note:- if n==0, we must return 0 as our answer. Here dp[0] = 1 for calculation.**

```
class Solution {
public:
    #define ll long long
    #define MOD 1000000007
    int numTilings(int n) {
        vector<ll> dp(n+1);
        iota(dp.begin(),dp.end(),0);
        dp[0] = 1;
        for(int i=3;i<=n;i++)
            dp[i] = (dp[i-1]+dp[i-1]+dp[i-3])%MOD;
        return dp.back();
    }
};
```

