Use two arrays for dp, `up[i]` means the board is complete from `0` to `i-1` , only the `i-th` column has only one square, `ret[i]` means the board is compelte from `0` to `i`.
See the picture for clarification.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/liyz1997/image_1558428660.png)

```
const int maxn = 1e9 + 7;
class Solution {
public:
    int numTilings(int N) {
        vector<long long> up(N + 1, 0), ret(N + 1, 0);
        ret[0] = 1;  // empty considered 1 way
        for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
			// for up[i]
            up[i] += up[i - 1];  // case 1
            if (i > 1)  // case 2
                up[i] += ret[i - 2];

            // for ret[i]
            ret[i] += ret[i - 1];  // case 1
            ret[i] += (2 * up[i - 1]);  // case 2
            if (i > 1)  // case 3
                ret[i] += ret[i - 2];

            up[i] %= maxn;
            ret[i] %= maxn;
        }
        return ret[N];
    }
};
```

