# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The value starts repeating after 4.
1 -> 1
2 -> 2
3 -> 5
4 -> 11 -> (2 X 5)+1
5 -> 24 -> (2 X 11)+1
6 -> 53 -> (2 X 24)+5
7 -> 117 -> (2 X 53)+11
8 -> 258 -> (2 X 117)+24
9 -> 569 -> (2 X 258)+53
10 -> 1255 -> (2 X 569)+117

formula = 2*a[n-1]+a[n-3]

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We are taking list of size 4. Therefore, The size complexity is O(1).

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int numTilings(int n) {
        list<long> l;
        l.push_back(1);
        for(int i=1;i<=n;i++)
            if(i < 3)
                l.push_back(i);
            else {
                int t = l.front();
                l.pop_front();
                l.push_back((2*l.back() + t)%1000000007);
            }
        return l.back();
    }
};
```

