# Observation
n ---> no. of ways
1 ---> 1
2 ---> 2
3 ---> 5
4 ---> 11
5 ---> 24
6 ---> 53

# Approach
As per the Observation we can formulate it as
```ans(n) = 2 * ans(n - 1) + ans(n - 3);```

# Code
```
//Memoization
class Solution {
const int mod = 1e9+7;
public:
    int solve(int n, vector<int>& dp){
        //base case
        if(n == 2 || n == 1)
            return n;
        if(n == 3)
            return 5;

        //DP table
        if(dp[n] != -1)
            return dp[n];

        return dp[n] = ((2 * solve(n-1, dp)) % mod + solve(n - 3, dp) % mod) % mod;
    }

    int numTilings(int n) {
        vector<int> dp(n+1, -1);
        return solve(n, dp);
    }
};

//Time Complexity : O(N)
//Space Complexity : O(N+1 + N)
```
