solutions.content:
If you see the values for n, like (n = 1 ans  = 1), (n = 2 ans = 2), (n = 3 ans = 5), (n = 4 ans = 11), (n = 5 ans = 24), (n=6 ans = 53)....
We can observe that in general for n, ans[n] = 2*(ans[n-1]) + ans[n-3]
Now this is simple DP problem!!

***C++ Solution:***
```
class Solution {
public:
    int numTilings(int n) {

        vector<long long> dp(1001,0);
        dp[1]=1, dp[2]=2, dp[3]=5;

        if(n<=3)
            return dp[n];

        for(int i=4;i<=n;++i)
            dp[i]=(2*dp[i-1]+dp[i-3])%1000000007; 

        return dp[n];
    }
};
```

***Java Solution:***
```
class Solution {
    public int numTilings(int n) {
        if(n<=2) 
            return n;

        int[] dp=new int[n+1];
        int mod = (int)(Math.pow(10,9)+7);
        dp[0]=1;dp[1]=1;dp[2]=2;

		for(int i=3;i<=n;i++) {
            dp[i]=(2*dp[i-1])%mod+dp[i-3];
            dp[i]%=mod;
        }

        return dp[n];
    }
}
```
***Time:*** O(n) ***Space:*** O(n)

But what if we want to decrease space too.... 🧐🤔

We can observe that ans[n] is just being dependent on ans[n-1] and ans[n-3]. So we will take 4 variables (namely one, two, three, res). Now we can store dp[1], dp[2], dp[3] into one, two, three variables resp. And res = 2 * three + one. Thats it!!!

***C++ Solution:***
```
class Solution {
public:
    int numTilings(int n) {

        long long one=1, two=2, three=5, total;

        if (n==1)
            return one;
        if (n==2)
            return two;
        if (n==3)
            return three;

        for(int i=4; i<=n; i++){
            total = (2*three + one)%1000000007;
            one = two;
            two = three;
            three = total;
        }

        return total%1000000007;
    }
};
```

***Java Solution:***
```
class Solution {
    public int numTilings(int n) {
        int one=1, two=2, three=5, total=0;

        if (n==1)
            return 1;
        if (n==2)
            return 2;
        if (n==3)
            return 5;

        for(int i=4; i<=n; i++){
            total = (2*three%1000000007 + one)%1000000007;
            one = two;
            two = three;
            three = total;
        }

        return total;
    }
}
```

***Time:*** O(n)         ***Space:*** O(1)

