dp[i][j] is the maximum number of stones Alex can get when starting at index i with M = j
sum[i] is the total number of stones from index i to the end
The dp matrix for Bob is the same, and the stragegy for Alex is to choose an optimal X to minimize the number of stones Bob can get when starting at index (i + X) with M = max(X,j), recurrence formula

```
dp[i][j] = max(dp[i][j], sum[i] - dp[i + X][max(j, X)]) where (1 <= X <= 2*j);
