solutions.content:
As we have to distribute total stones between Person1 & Person2.
        If we maximize difference between them, then we will get maximum Person1 can get (minimum Person2 can get)
        ->Person1+Person2=sum_of_stones_in_piles.
        -> We caluculate maximum difference.int max_diff=Person1-Person2=dfs()
        Person1=(sum_of_stones_in_piles+max_diff)/2,Person2=sum_of_stones_in_piles-Person1.
->Here as both players play optimally and as they will be switching,so at every instance we try to find maximum possible score by selecting 1 to 2*M from start. and **add** it to score if it is Player1 or **subtract** if it is Player2.
->So as we are finding difference between Person1 & Person2. **-DFS** will be called even no.of times for Player1 and odd no.of times for Player2,So value of picked stone will get **added** for Player1 and **subtracted** for Player2.
Here as -dfs() takes care of whether adding/subtracting , dfs(index,M) will be same irrespective of the person. So we can use a hashMap to store already computed results and **add** it to current diff if it is Person_1 or **subtract** if it is Person2.
->dfs(start,M) gives
Person1=selects_stones-dfs(Person2=select_stones-dfs(Person1=select_stones-dfs(.....)))
At the end we can see that, (sum of stones of Person1)- (sum of stones of Person2)
```
class Solution {
    int[] prefix_sum;
    int[] piles;
    int n;
    HashMap<String,Integer> memo=new HashMap();
    public int stoneGameII(int[] nums) {
        n=nums.length;prefix_sum=new int[n];piles=nums;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
            prefix_sum[i]=piles[i]+((i==0)?0:prefix_sum[i-1]);
        int max_diff=dfs(0,1);
        return (prefix_sum[n-1]+max_diff)/2;
    }
    private int dfs(int start,int M){
        if(start>=n) return 0;
		/*If total-range of values <=2*M,then
		to get maximum score current_player will take all the stones in this range.*/
        if(n-start<=2*M) return prefix_sum[n-1]-((start==0)?0:prefix_sum[start-1]);
        String key=start+" "+M;
        if(memo.containsKey(key)) return memo.get(key);
        int res=Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(int k=1;k<=2*M;k++)
		//Select the maximum difference
            res=Math.max(res,
			/*Current_player takes k-stones and calls -dfs() for next person*/
                         (prefix_sum[start+k-1]-((start==0)?0:prefix_sum[start-1]))
                         -dfs(start+k,Math.max(M,k)));
        memo.put(key,res);
        return res;

    }
}
```
